</taxonomicName>
(Europe), 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D51FF80176FFCAD6ADCAE9CFF58" authority="Koenike" authorityName="Koenike" box="[886,1152,188,213]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Pionacercus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uncinatus">
<emphasis id="B907EAC0FF80176FFCAD6ADCAE1FFF59" box="[886,1027,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">P. uncinatus</emphasis>
(Koenike)
</taxonomicName>
(Europe), 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D51FF80176FFADA6ADCAAD1FF75" authority="Thor" authorityName="Thor" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Pionacercus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="norvegicus">
<emphasis id="B907EAC0FF80176FFADA6ADCAF80FF59" box="[1281,1436,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">P. norvegicus</emphasis>
Thor
</taxonomicName>
(Europe), 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D51FF80176FFE8A6A80A859FF7A" authority="Imamura" authorityName="Imamura" box="[337,581,224,248]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Pionacercus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonica">
<emphasis id="B907EAC0FF80176FFE8A6A80ABC8FF75" box="[337,468,225,248]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">P. japonica</emphasis>
Imamura
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry id="F3647642FF80176FFD816A81A8BCFF75" box="[602,672,224,248]" name="Japan" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">Japan</collectingCountry>
). There are five undescribed species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D51FF80176FFB5B6A80AF17FF75" box="[1152,1291,225,248]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Pionacercus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B907EAC0FF80176FFB5B6A80AF17FF75" box="[1152,1291,225,248]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">Pionacercus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from North 
<collectingCountry id="F3647642FF80176FFF4C6B65AAEBFE90" box="[151,247,260,285]" name="United States of America" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">America</collectingCountry>
in the Canadian National Collection of Insects and Arachnids and larvae have been associated with adults by rearing for one of them. One of these species is also represented in the Habeeb Collection and was incorrectly reported as 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D51FF80176FFEC26B2CA882FEE8" authority="Piersig (Habeeb 1958)" authorityName="Piersig (Habeeb" authorityYear="1958" box="[281,670,332,357]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Pionacercus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leuckarti">
<emphasis id="B907EAC0FF80176FFEC26B2CAB85FEE8" box="[281,409,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">P. leuckarti</emphasis>
Piersig (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE24B23FF80176FFE276B2DA88AFEE8" author="Habeeb" box="[508,662,332,357]" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" refString="Habeeb, H. (1958) New mites from New Brunswick. Leaflets of Acadian Biology, 18, 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="1958">
Habeeb 
<number id="3DBB24F5FF80176FFD816B2DA88AFEE8" box="[602,662,332,357]" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" value="1958.0">1958</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3696559FF80176FFF1C6B0EA8E7FE05" box="[199,763,367,392]" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BCC36D2FF80176FFF1C6B0EA8E7FE05" blockId="8.[151,1436,151,608]" box="[199,763,367,392]" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">
<emphasis id="B907EAC0FF80176FFF1C6B0EAB7CFE05" bold="true" box="[199,352,367,392]" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">Distribution.</emphasis>
Holarctic (Eurasia, North 
<collectingCountry id="F3647642FF80176FFD516B0EA8ECFE05" box="[650,752,367,392]" name="United States of America" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">America</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3696559FF80176FFF1C6BF5A974FDED" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BCC36D2FF80176FFF1C6BF5A974FDED" blockId="8.[151,1436,151,608]" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">
<emphasis id="B907EAC0FF80176FFF1C6BF5AB50FE20" bold="true" box="[199,332,404,429]" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">Discussion.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE24B23FF80176FFE836BF5ABE5FE21" author="Cook" box="[344,505,404,429]" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" refString="Cook, D. R. (1974 a) Water mite genera and subgenera. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 21, 1 - 860." type="journal article" year="1974" yearSuffix="a">
Cook (
<number id="3DBB24F5FF80176FFE716BF5ABF8FE21" box="[426,484,404,428]" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" value="1974.0">1974</number>
a)
</bibRefCitation>
treated 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D51FF80176FFD856BF4A8F5FE21" box="[606,745,405,428]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Pionacercus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B907EAC0FF80176FFD856BF4A8F5FE21" box="[606,745,405,428]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">Pionacercus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(including the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D51FF80176FFBC26BF4AED9FE21" box="[1049,1221,405,428]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Pionacercopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B907EAC0FF80176FFBC26BF4AED9FE21" box="[1049,1221,405,428]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">Pionacercopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) in the subfamily Tiphyinae. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE24B23FF80176FFECE6BD6ABB5FE5D" author="Smith" box="[277,425,439,464]" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" refString="Smith, I. M. (1976) A study of the systematics of the water mite family Pionidae (Prostigmata: Parasitengona). Memoirs of the Entomological Society of Canada, 98, 1 - 249." type="journal article" year="1976">
Smith (
<number id="3DBB24F5FF80176FFEBC6BD6ABBDFE5D" box="[359,417,439,464]" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" value="1976.0">1976</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
placed 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D51FF80176FFE246BD8A896FE5D" box="[511,650,441,464]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Pionacercus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B907EAC0FF80176FFE246BD8A896FE5D" box="[511,650,441,464]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">Pionacercus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(including 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D51FF80176FFCD16BD8A9AAFE5D" box="[778,950,441,464]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Pionacercopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B907EAC0FF80176FFCD16BD8A9AAFE5D" box="[778,950,441,464]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">Pionacercopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) in the tribe Foreliini along with the genera 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D51FF80176FFF4C6BBDAAF7FE78" box="[151,235,476,501]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Forelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B907EAC0FF80176FFF4C6BBDAAF7FE78" box="[151,235,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">Forelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D51FF80176FFEFC6BBDABA2FE78" box="[295,446,476,501]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Pseudofeltria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B907EAC0FF80176FFEFC6BBDABA2FE78" box="[295,446,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">Pseudofeltria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE24B23FF80176FFE0B6BBDA8D4FE79" author="Smith" box="[464,712,476,501]" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" refString="Smith, I. M. &amp; Cook, D. R. (1991) Water mites. Chapter 16. In: Thorp, J. &amp; Covich, A. (Eds.), Ecology and classification of North American freshwater invertebrates. Academic Press, San Diego, CA, pp. 523 - 592. [total page number 911 pp.]" type="book chapter" year="1991">Smith &amp; Cook (1991</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE24B23FF80176FFD0C6BBDA90CFE79" author="Smith" box="[727,784,476,500]" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" refString="Smith, I. M. &amp; Cook, D. R. (1999) An assessment of global distribution patterns in water mites (Acari: Hydrachnida). In: Needham, G. R., Mitchell, R. D., Horn, D. J. &amp; Welbourn, W. C. (Eds.), Acarology IX. Vol. 2. Symposia. Ohio Biological Survey, Columbus, pp. 109 - 124." type="book" year="1999">1999</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE24B23FF80176FFC8D6BBDAE32FE79" author="Smith" box="[854,1070,476,501]" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" refString="Smith, I. M., Cook, D. R. &amp; Smith, B. P. (2001) Water mites and other arachnids. Chapter 16. In: Thorpe, J. &amp; Covich, A. (Eds.), Ecology and classification of North American freshwater invertebrates. 2 nd Edition. Academic Press, Waltham, Massachusetts, pp. 551 - 659. [1056 pp.] http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1016 / B 978 - 012690647 - 9 / 50017 - X" type="book chapter" year="2001">
Smith 
<emphasis id="B907EAC0FF80176FFC7F6BBCA9CBFE78" box="[932,983,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">et al</emphasis>
. (2001
</bibRefCitation>
, 2010) treated this clade as the subfamily Foreliinae. Gerecke (
<number id="3DBB24F5FF80176FFDC86861A852FD95" box="[531,590,512,536]" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" value="2014.0">2014</number>
) proposed placing 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D51FF80176FFCE56860A9D5FD95" box="[830,969,513,536]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Pionacercus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B907EAC0FF80176FFCE56860A9D5FD95" box="[830,969,513,536]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">Pionacercus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D51FF80176FFBCA6860AEA1FD95" box="[1041,1213,513,536]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Pionacercopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B907EAC0FF80176FFBCA6860AEA1FD95" box="[1041,1213,513,536]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">Pionacercopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Foreliinae, apparently unaware that 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE24B23FF80176FFE6B6845A85AFDB0" author="Smith" box="[432,582,548,573]" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" refString="Smith, I. M. (1976) A study of the systematics of the water mite family Pionidae (Prostigmata: Parasitengona). Memoirs of the Entomological Society of Canada, 98, 1 - 249." type="journal article" year="1976">
Smith (
<number id="3DBB24F5FF80176FFDD86845A821FDB0" box="[515,573,548,573]" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" value="1976.0">1976</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
had already assigned them to Foreliini. Here we follow Gerecke (
<number id="3DBB24F5FF80176FFAE06845AF6AFDB1" box="[1339,1398,548,572]" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" value="2014.0">2014</number>
) in considering 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D51FF80176FFEFB6828ABB7FDED" box="[288,427,585,608]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Pionacercus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B907EAC0FF80176FFEFB6828ABB7FDED" box="[288,427,585,608]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">Pionacercus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D51FF80176FFE396828A892FDED" box="[482,654,585,608]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Pionacercopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B907EAC0FF80176FFE396828A892FDED" box="[482,654,585,608]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">Pionacercopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as separate genera.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
